11/06/2003
ANKARA, Turkey -- On Tuesday (10 June), the Council of Ministers approved the sixth EU adaptation package and will submit it to the National Assembly for approval.
The cabinet spent seven hours discussing the legislation harmonisation proposal and approved it only after a controversial article was dropped.
It would have permitted places of worship in apartment buildings.
Turkish Foreign Minister Abdullah Gul said afterwards that the military has no serious objections.
(Anadolu Agency, NTV, TRT 2, AFP - 10/06/03)
